    worst_review:
      "This computer has an extremely sensitive auto-rotate function which cannot be adjusted/toggled in Settings. As a result, this computer will make you scream out loud in frustration. You will be sitting down, and all of a sudden the auto-rotate will be activated, and the keyboard is useless and you can only use the device as a touch screen. God forbid you move the computer--it really doesn't like that. Sometimes I need to restart the computer entirely; other times restarting doesn't even help. I am a student and I need to be able to type. However, it seems that this is too high a request. Each session, I spend an inordinate amount of time trying to get the computer out of \"auto-rotate hell\", during which I waste time and I can't get anything done. Do yourself a favor and stay away from this device, and for that matter, probably this entire line in general. It's a total gimmick, its extremely glitchy and sloppy, and you will waste time both troubleshooting and when you inevitably attempt to get a refund.",
